text: 저기 숙제하다가 안 풀려서 그런데 질문해도 되나요?

그러면 한 번 써 볼께요. 지금 Matrix addition문제를 풀고 있는데요. 문제는 다음과 같아요.
There is a N  N matrix A initialized by arbitary values. Suppose that we have to add N
submatrices to A as follows:

for i := 1 to N do
    read (Ri;1;Ri;2;Ci;1;Ci;2; Vi);
    for i := Ri;1 to Ri;2 do
        for j := Ci;1 to Ci;2 do
            A[i][j] := A[i][j] + Vi;
        end
    end
end
Values Ri;1, Ri;2, Ci;1, Ci;2, and Vi are different from submatrix to submatrix. We have
0  <= Ri;1;Ri;2;Ci;1;Ci;2 <=  N. Thus, this program takes O(N^3) time. How can we improve
this? Design a more efficient method.
